						               													<description>Image is a trivia game in the 3M Bookshelf Series where the players have a historical or fictional character in mind and then they play cards which describes the person:&amp;#10;- Place where they lived or were born (Albert Schweitzer was born in France and known in his work in Africa so France, Europe, Africa are all good.)&amp;#10;- Time when they lived (for Scheitzer, 19th and 20th Centuries)&amp;#10;- Activity: (Schweitzer was well known in Medicine, Music, Religion, Exploration, etc.)&amp;#10;- Status cards: (Living/Dead, Fictional/nonFictional, etc.)&amp;#10;- The first letter of their last name. This action closes the image and it scores for the player who played the letter card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The players score points for the number of cards played on an image. You may play a card on another player's image (and thus possibly steal it.) And an image can be challenged and if the player has no one in mind, he is penalized.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The deck contains 112 cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
